    </td>
    <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:1.5pt 1.5pt 1.5pt 1.5pt'>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal><span =
style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;
    color:#333333'>Some key observations investors need to =
consider:</span></p>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>1.<span
    style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New =
Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>Price =
represents
    the fair market value as agreed between buyers (bulls) and sellers =
(bears).
    </span></p>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>2.<span
    style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New =
Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>Changes in =
price
    are the result of changes in investor expectations of the security's =
future
    price. </span></p>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>3.<span
    style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New =
Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>Support =
levels
    occur when the consensus is that the price will not move lower. It =
is the
    point where buyers outnumber sellers. </span></p>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>4.<span
    style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New =
Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>Resistance =
levels
    occur when the consensus is that the price will not move higher. It =
is the
    point where sellers outnumber buyers. </span></p>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>5.<span
    style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New =
Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>The =
penetration of
    a support or resistance level indicates a change in investor =
expectations
    and a shift in the supply/demand lines. </span></p>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>6.<span
    style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New =
Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>Volume is =
useful in
    determining how strong the change of expectations really is. =
</span></p>
    <p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>7.<span
    style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New =
Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
    style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333'>Traders' =
remorse
    often follows the penetration of a support or resistance level as =
prices
    retreat to the penetrated level. Which means what? The sellers feel =
stupid
    for having sold and want back in! </span></p>
    </td>
