    <p class=3DMsoNormal><span =
style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Arial;
    color:#333333'>If one looks at the 4-year chart, effectively =
covering the
    double-bottom of early 2001 and the full move of this first phase of =
what
    is now a new secular bull market, a clear channel can be plotted =
which
    bounds the higher-lows and higher-highs with parallel up-trend =
lines.
    Today, to break the bottom trend line we would need to see price =
break down
    through the $390 area, and then there still exists major support at =
the old
    resistance band around the $375 level. A break in the established =
uptrend
    would not negate the bull market, but a breakdown through major =
support
    would put it in jeopardy - effectively the lows of April 2004 would =
need to
    be breached to the downside.</span></p>
